Description: Digital photograph (colour); view of engraved rock art on stone block showing figures of one human, three elephants, one unidentified quadruped, a falcon, three ostriches, two cows and hieroglyphic text, all pecked in outline and upright. Elephant is central and largest, naturalistic with infilled body and ear lacking infill. Smaller similar elephant to lower right. Between elephants, crossing larger elephant’s left foot is unidentified quadruped (head not visible) pecked in outline. Behind this is a stylised falcon. To upper left are two ostriches facing right and to lower left two cows facing one another with long horns. Several unidentified shapes surround figure with several hieroglyphs at left and large elephant’s trunk superimposing further ostrich figure. At the far left of the image is the had and trunk of a stylised elephant. New Kalabsha, Egypt. Scanned
Acquisition name: Donated by: Trust for African Rock Art
